// BT-2206: E2E fixture for `SystemNavigation unimplementedSelectors`.
//
// `DnuDispatcher` defines `doesNotUnderstand:args:`, so it can legitimately
// receive arbitrary selectors via `self`. The `dispatch` method sends a
// uniquely-named undefined selector to `self`; the typo-finder's coarse DNU
// heuristic must NOT flag it (the DNU handler interprets it dynamically).

Object subclass: DnuDispatcher

  // Intercepts any unrecognised message — this is what makes self-sends of
  // undefined selectors legitimate for this class.
  doesNotUnderstand: selector :: Symbol args: arguments :: Array -> Object =>
    @expect type
    selector

  // Sends `dnuOnlyHandledSelectorXyzzy` to self. Defined nowhere, but routed
  // through this class's DNU handler at runtime, so it must not be flagged.
  dispatch =>
    @expect dnu
    self dnuOnlyHandledSelectorXyzzy
